keyValuePair.Value: Any special plans?
It's a massive game, a Final, and the extra edge is that you're playing your great rivals, %1s. With all that in mind, have you made any special plans for handling the big day?
It's all motivation!
It's all motivation!
Special plans? Not at all. We've prepared well and now we'll go out and play our football. The lads are looking forward to the challenge. And to taking on our great rivals, too!
We're always ready!
We're always ready!
We're under no illusions. Playing %1s always means you're in for a tough game. But we haven't made any special plans. These players are always ready to take on the next challenge.
We're under no illusions. Playing %1s always means you're in for a tough game. But we haven't made any special plans. These players are always ready to take on the next challenge.
We'll prepare as we always do.
We know what we want to achieve and we know how we'll be able to do it. Yes, a few tactical changes and maybe one or two new faces in the starting line-up. But we'll play as we always do.
Is fitness an issue here?
You're up against %1s in the Final, a really strong team. After you've come through such a demanding run of games, are you worried fatigue might be an issue today?
It's the same for both teams.
At this stage of the season, every successful team will have played a lot of games. If fatigue's an issue for us, it will be for our opponents as well. That won't be the decisive factor here.

Some of the lads are struggling.
The lads have played a lot of football lately and one or two of them are feeling it a bit. How important a factor fatigue's going to be, though, we won't know till the Final gets underway.
We've worked so hard to be here.
It's been a fantastic team effort to reach the Final. And we don't want to make excuses for ourselves. The lads can't wait. We'll have a good go and worry about feeling tired afterwards!

Will %1s make it a physical battle?
On paper, %1s look the team with less technical quality in their ranks. Do you think they may try to compensate for that by turning the game into a physical battle?
The lads will be ready.
The lads will be ready.
We know what we need to do. Whatever kind of game the opposition want to make of it, my boys will be ready to deal with that challenge.
We know what we need to do. Whatever kind of game the opposition want to make of it, my boys will be ready to deal with that challenge.
The lads can handle themselves.
My team will go out and play their football. If the game gets physical, I've no worries. They can handle that side of things, too.
We managed to get to this final with a rather stable starting 11. I won't make changes that are not necessary.
We'll play our game.
We know exactly how we want to approach the game. What the opposition do is up to them. It won't distract us from what we plan to do.
Are you worried about under-estimating %1s?
All the talk before the game has been about your team being stronger than %1s. Are you worried your players may go into it underestimating the opposition?
We still have a job to do.
If we go out and play our football and have a professional attitude to the game, I've no worries. Other people may underestimate our opponents, but we won't.
The lads have been here before.
This is an experienced group of players. They've been in this situation before. They won't let any complacency undermine the job they have to do.
It's about what we do.
I'm not concerned about how people rate our opponents. That doesn't come into it for my players. All our focus is on our own performance.
Will you make changes to the line-up?
You're going into the %1s Final as underdogs against %2s. With that in mind, can we expect changes to your starting line-up or even unexpected faces to be on the bench?
We're all in this together.
Whoever I select in the starting line-up, I know they'll give me 100%. This team's better than people think and we've got a winning mentality. Let's go out and prove people wrong now!
Whoever I select in the starting line-up, I know they'll give me 100%. This team's better than people think and we've got a winning mentality. Let's go out and prove people wrong now!
We've been in this position before.
This is isn't new to us. We've been underdogs before. In fact, we've won games against even stronger teams than today's opponents. It's a cup final. We'll be ready for it!
We'll try to rise to the occasion.
We've been in battles like this one before. I hope we've got enough quality to make a game of it. It's a cup final and I'm confident my boys can rise to the occasion.
How can you come out on top?
You go into this %1s Final against %2s with most people rating them the stronger outfit. What are your plans? How can you overturn expectations and secure a %3s win?
The pressure's all on them.
Being the underdogs doesn't worry us. In fact, it means the pressure is all on %1s. We've got nothing to lose here and that can give us the freedom to put in a great performance, I'm sure.
Whatever changes will occur, all my lads are professional.
Hard work's already brought us this far.

To be fair, nobody fancied us to get this far in the competition, so it's nothing new for us to go into the Final as underdogs now. It's about hard work for us. I think we can pull off another surprise.
